 for bestpractices and # Calendar / Week View

## Overview
Build a premium, interactive Calendar / Week View within the LuxeFlow CRM to manage check-ins, check-outs, key booking deadlines, tasks, and room blocks. The page supports filtering by agent, resort, and booking status, and enables drag-to-reschedule for permitted operations. It integrates with the project’s Calendar Sync & Scheduling feature, offering one-way and two-way Google Calendar / iCal synchronization and iCal export. All UI adheres to the LuxeFlow design system with a luxury, calm, and highly usable experience.

## Page Description (Full Detail)
What this page is:
- A Week View (with optional Day/Week toggle) calendar that visualizes time-bound events across multiple categories: guest check-ins, guest check-outs, key booking deadlines (payments, deadlines, approvals), internal tasks, and room blocks (block/reserve rooms for operations or VIP stays). It provides horizontal time alignment and lanes per resource (rooms, agents, or resorts) and supports drag-and-drop rescheduling for certain event types (e.g., check-ins, room blocks, and task deadlines when permitted by permissions and business rules).

Goals:
- Offer an at-a-glance, highly interactive schedule that surfaces time-critical items for the upcoming 7 days (default), with the ability to drill into event details, link quickly to a Booking Detail page, and perform quick actions (mark as complete, reassign, adjust deadlines).
- Provide robust filtering to focus on subsets: by agent, by resort, and by booking status (e.g., Pending, Confirmed, Payment Due, Overdue).
- Enable drag-to-reschedule for reschedulable events with built-in validations (permissions, business rules, conflicts, and capacity checks). Validate before commit and present non-blocking, contextual feedback for the user.
- Integrate with Calendar Sync & Scheduling: one-way and two-way sync with Google Calendar and iCal, plus direct iCal export. Include per-user sync settings, sync status indicators, and conflict resolution flows.
- Ensure data integrity and safety with strict runtime checks, guarding against null/undefined results from API calls and Supabase queries.

UI elements and visual guidance:
- Week/Day toggle controls with prominent state indication
- Event blocks styled by type (check-in, check-out, deadline, task, room block)
- Drag handles and drop targets with validation prompts
- Filters panel: multi-select for agents, resorts, and status chips for booking status
- Event Detail Popover with quick actions: Open Booking Detail, Edit Event, Mark as Complete, and Link to related Booking
- Sync panel: Add to Google Calendar, iCal Export, and preferences for one-way/two-way sync
- Quick-create actions for common tasks (e.g., add a new room block or deadline)

Connected features:
- Calendar Sync & Scheduling: Sync booking milestones and agent schedules with Google Calendar / iCal. Provide one-way and two-way sync options and iCal exports.

Visual guidance:
- Maintain the LuxeFlow luxury aesthetic: clean white surfaces, olive accent color, warm neutrals, serif headings, sans-serif body text, generous whitespace, and tactile hover/focus states.

## Components to Build
- CalendarWeekView
  - Props: events[], filters{agentIds, resortIds, status}, viewMode ('week'|'day'), dateRange, dragSettings
  - State: hoveredEventId, activeEventId, selectedFilters, dragState
  - Subcomponents:
    - TimeScaleColumn (hours of day)
    - ResourceLane (per room/agent/resort)
    - EventCard (type-based styling, drag handle if allowed)
    - EventPopover (detail and quick actions)
    - FilterPanel (agent, resort, status)
    - DragContextLayer (handles drag operations with validation)
    - QuickActionsBar (sync/export, add event)
    - SyncPanel (Google Calendar / iCal toggles and status)
- EventCard variants
  - CheckInCard, CheckOutCard, DeadlineCard, TaskCard, RoomBlockCard
  - Each card shows title, time window, associated booking, status, and action buttons
- BookingDetailLink
  - Lightweight link to Booking detail page with prefilled anchor (scroll-to)
- DragAndDropEngine
  - Handles drag start, drag over, drop, and validation against business rules
  - Ensures runtime safety: checks on arrays, nullish data, and permissions
- FilterBar
  - Multi-select dropdowns for agents and resorts
  - Status chips with clear and filter-by-action behavior
- SyncPanel
  - Google Calendar / iCal integration UI
  - Per-user sync settings, one-way vs two-way, and export actions
- API Integration Layer
  - Fetch calendar events, bookings, rooms, agents, and statuses with validated shapes
  - Endpoint wrappers that guard against nulls and non-arrays
- DetailPopover
  - Shows event details and quick navigation to related Booking

Technical details for implementation:
- Data adapters must normalize API responses. Always validate:
  - const events = Array.isArray(response?.data?.events) ? response.data.events : []
  - const bookings = Array.isArray(response?.data?.bookings) ? response.data.bookings : []
- Use data ?? [] for Supabase results
- Guard all array operations:
  - (events ?? []).map(...)
  - Array.isArray(events) ? events.filter(...) : []
- useState defaults for arrays:
  - const [events, setEvents] = useState<Event[]>([])
  - const [filters, setFilters] = useState<Filters>({ agentIds: [], resortIds: [], status: [] })
- Optional chaining for nested associations:
  - event?.booking?.id, booking?.resort?.name
- Destructure with defaults:
  - const { items = [], count = 0 } = response ?? {}

## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend
- UI components
  - Week/day calendar grid with time slots in 30-minute increments
  - Lanes for rooms and agents; support horizontal scrolling for wide views
  - Event blocks with color-coding by type and status
  - Drag-and-drop with:
    - Visual drag cue
    - Validation: user permission, event type, business rules, conflicts
    - On drop, present confirmation modal if necessary and then commit
  - Event detail popovers with:
    - Booking link, status, deadlines
    - Quick actions: edit, reschedule, mark complete, view booking
  - Filters panel with accessible controls and keyboard navigation
  - Sync controls and iCal export actions
- Accessibility
  - Keyboard navigable, ARIA roles for calendar grid, events, and dialogs
  - High-contrast focus styles, readable typography, and responsive behavior
- State management
  - Local UI state for drag, popovers, and filter selections
  - Global data fetch and cache for calendar events, bookings, and related entities
- Performance
  - Virtualized rendering for large date ranges
  - Debounced filter changes and pagination where applicable

### Backend
- APIs
  - GET /calendar/events?range=YYYY-MM-DD..YYYY-MM-DD&agentIds=&resortIds=&status=
  - GET /bookings/{id}
  - GET /agents, GET /resorts, GET /rooms
  - POST /calendar/events (create)
  - PATCH /calendar/events/{id} (update, including reschedule)
  - DELETE /calendar/events/{id} (optional)
  - GET /calendar/sync/status (per-user)
  - POST /calendar/sync/setup (one-way/two-way, google/ical)
  - GET /ical/export?bookingId=
- Database schema (key tables)
  - calendar_events: id, type (checkin, checkout, deadline, task, room_block), start_at, end_at, booking_id, room_id, agent_id, resort_id, status, title, notes, created_by, updated_by
  - bookings: id, client_id, resort_id, room_type, check_in, check_out, payment_schedule, status, etc.
  - rooms: id, number, resort_id, block_status
  - agents: id, name, email, permissions
  - resorts: id, name, location, transfer_time, policies
  - tasks: id, booking_id, due_at, status, assignee_id
  - calendar_syncs: id, user_id, provider, sync_type, last_sync_at, config
- Security
  - JWT-based authentication with role checks (Admin, Agent, Ops, Finance)
  - Resource-level permissions for viewing/editing calendar events
- Validation
  - Ensure required fields for create/update
  - Validate date ranges, non-overlapping blocks when business rules forbid overlaps
  - Validate user permissions before mutating events
  - Validate API responses against expected shapes; sanitize inputs

### Integration
- Data flow
  - CalendarWeekView fetches events/bookings/rooms/agents/resorts
  - Drag-and-drop updates trigger PATCH to calendar_events and update related booking deadlines when needed
  - Filtering triggers re-fetch or client-side filtering of the events array
  - SyncPanel configures Google Calendar / iCal sync; triggers backend sync jobs or webhooks
- Sync logic
  - One-way: from LuxeFlow to Google/Calendar or iCal feed
  - Two-way: sync from Google/Calendar back into LuxeFlow with conflict resolution prompts
  - iCal export: generate and serve .ics with event details and recurrence if applicable
- Data consistency
  - Use optimistic UI updates with rollback on error
  - Ensure all data mutations guard against null/undefined values

## User Experience Flow
1. User lands on Calendar / Week View
   - Sees week view with days and hourly grid
   - Left/top toolbars provide Week/Day toggle, filters, and quick actions
2. Filtering
   - User selects agents, resorts, and statuses; view updates to show relevant events
   - If no events match, show a friendly empty state with guidance
3. Event interaction
   - Hovering an event reveals quick actions (open, reschedule, link to booking)
   - Drag an event to a new time Slot or day (if allowed)
   - On drop, validation occurs; if valid, event saves and a subtle confirmation appears
   - If invalid, a non-blocking error toast explains why
4. Event detail
   - Click/tap opens Event Detail Popover with booking link and quick actions
5. Synchronization
   - User opens SyncPanel and configures Google Calendar / iCal
   - Choose one-way or two-way sync; enable and authorize as needed
   - iCal export generates a downloadable .ics file
6. Navigation
   - Use the top navigation to switch to Booking Detail or other CRM areas
   - Drag-and-drop interactions provide visual feedback, respecting responsive constraints

